00:41:37,001 --> 00:41:37,445
Scott: canon.".

617
00:41:38,211 --> 00:41:40,525
Scott: And so the TV show is also canon.

618
00:41:40,786 --> 00:41:41,350
Scott: It's all canon.

619
00:41:41,730 --> 00:41:47,670
Rym: In fact, based on at least the first three movies, "canon" with a capital C, and I'll leave it at that.

620
00:41:48,832 --> 00:41:52,870
Scott: Everything that happened in the TV show happened and everything in this happened, even though it's not a sequel.

621
00:41:53,950 --> 00:41:58,570
Scott: And that'll only make sense if you've seen it all, which is why it's okay to just say that.

622
00:41:58,732 --> 00:41:59,830
Scott: It's not spoiling anything.

623
00:42:01,010 --> 00:42:08,830
Scott: But whether the movies... I actually like the TV show way more than the movies still, even having seen all four of the movies.

624
00:42:08,890 --> 00:42:11,490
Rym: But I liked the movies nearly equally.

625
00:42:12,850 --> 00:42:21,570
Scott: But what I think is great about the rebuild and why I think maybe someone else will attempt a rebuild of something else at some point.

626
00:42:21,710 --> 00:42:23,348
Scott: I don't know if any... I can't think of anyone who has.

627
00:42:23,670 --> 00:42:35,150
Rym: The nearest thing I can think of, but it's such a poor analogy because these tended to be garbage, was there was a number of 90s anime that had an OAV that was very popular.

628
00:42:35,630 --> 00:42:42,270
Rym: And then they would make an alternate universe where they tell the same story again as a longer TV show to explore an alternate set of events.

629
00:42:43,072 --> 00:42:44,450
Scott: Yeah, but that's an alternate universe.

630
00:42:46,172 --> 00:42:48,760
Rym: And also, they didn't really have the same messages.

631
00:42:48,860 --> 00:42:51,990
Rym: They were mostly just bad and watered down.

632
00:42:52,070 --> 00:42:52,920
Scott: You know what's comparable?

633
00:42:52,961 --> 00:42:53,690
Scott: You know what's comparable?

634
00:42:54,310 --> 00:42:55,070
Scott: Zelda's comparable.

635
00:42:56,612 --> 00:43:02,290
Scott: Zelda games is like, yeah, there was a book that had some sequence of timelines or whatever in it or something.

636
00:43:02,630 --> 00:43:07,249
Scott: But all the Zelda games are mostly separate, taking place in different...

637
00:43:07,570 --> 00:43:12,009
Rym: But they explore a very similar story, a very similar universe, a very similar...

